55.8	Relic	Relic	In religion, a relic is a part of the body of a saint or a venerated person, or else another type of ancient religious object, carefully preserved for purposes of veneration or as a tangible memorial. Relics are an important aspect of some forms of Buddhism, Christianity, Hinduism, Shamanism, and many other religions.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Reliekschrijnbinnen.jpg/300px-Reliekschrijnbinnen.jpg
